        <p>NHS blue is the dominant colour in the NHS colour palette. We use it for <a href="/patterns/header/">the header</a>, links, <a href="/patterns/care-cards/">care cards</a> and<a href="/patterns/inset_text/"> inset text.</a></p>

        <p>White is used to make important information stand out and for alternating backgrounds, for example on the <a href="https://www.nhs.uk/">NHS.UK home page</a>.</p>


        <p>We use:</p>
          <ul>
              <li>red for urgency, and negative or destructive actions, for example in <a href="/service-manual/patterns/care-cards/#urgent-care-red">urgent and emergency care cards</a></li>
